{
  "texts": [
    "Results on specific infections and antibiotic characteristics demonstrate the models have stable performance across numerous different patient groups.",
    "Particularly important is understanding when oral antibiotics with incomplete absorption can be used, given concerns surrounding achieving therapeutic concentrations.",
    "Our long model achieved an AUROC of 0.77 (SD 0.02) in this subpopulation.",
    "Furthermore, in conditions such as sepsis where patients are criticallyill for prolonged periods and fewer oral therapies are utilised, our short model obtained an AUROC of 0.82 (SD 0.02).",
    "Indicating that such a support system could be utilised in severe infections."
  ]
}